!function(){"use strict";function e(e,t,n,o,a,c){function r(n){var r=t[0].querySelectorAll(".sound-container")[n];u=angular.element(r.querySelector(".resize-container")),l=u.scope().sound,o.selectSound({target:r},l),u.addClass("hover"),c.trackSection||(c.trackSection=e.workspace.trackSection),a.onResizeStart(l,{element:u,width:u[0].offsetWidth})}function i(e){var t=u[0].clientWidth,n=t*e;a.onResize(l,{element:u,width:n})}function s(){n(function(){a.onResizeEnd(l,{element:u},{stopPropagation:angular.noop})})}var l,u;e.instructions=[function(){e.workspace.trackSection.addSound(e.workspace.trackSection.beat(1,1),{start:.25,string:"A",style:"slap",note:{type:"regular",name:"B",octave:1,fret:2,length:16}}),e.workspace.trackSection.addSound(e.workspace.trackSection.beat(1,2),{start:.25,string:"A",style:"slap",note:{type:"regular",name:"C",octave:2,fret:3,length:16}}),e.workspace.trackSection.addSound(e.workspace.trackSection.beat(1,2),{start:.5,string:"A",style:"slap",note:{type:"regular",name:"E",octave:2,fret:7,length:16}})},function(){r(0)},function(){i(3)},function(){s()},function(){o.clearSelection(),u.removeClass("hover")},function(){r(1)},function(){i(2)},function(){s()},function(){o.clearSelection(),e.workspace.trackSection.clearBeat(e.workspace.trackSection.beat(1,1)),e.workspace.trackSection.clearBeat(e.workspace.trackSection.beat(1,2))}]}e.$inject=["$scope","$element","$timeout","basicHandler","bassResizeHandler","workspace"],angular.module("bd.help").controller("ResizeSlideshow",e)}();
!function(){"use strict";function e(e,t,o,n,c,a){var r,s,i;e.instructions=[function(){r={start:.5,string:"G",volume:.75,style:"finger",note:{type:"regular",name:"A",octave:2,code:"A2",fret:2,length:16}},e.workspace.trackSection.addSound(e.workspace.trackSection.beat(1,1),r)},function(){s=t[0].querySelector(".sound-container"),i=c.open({target:s},r,{clickOutsideToClose:!1,escapeToClose:!1,attachTo:t.parent(),panelClass:"non-interactive bass-form"})},function(){r.note.dotted=!0,r.end=r.start+e.workspace.trackSection.soundDuration(r)},function(){r.note.staccato=!0},function(){i&&(i.close(),i=null),n.clearSelection(),e.workspace.trackSection.clearBeat(e.workspace.trackSection.beat(1,1))}]}e.$inject=["$scope","$element","$timeout","basicHandler","bassSoundForm","$mdCompiler"],angular.module("bd.help").controller("SoundPropertiesSlideshow",e)}();
angular.module("templates").run(["$templateCache",function(n){n.put("views/help/app.html",'<section\n  id="section-1"\n  style="padding-top:44px;">\n  <h4 style="top:20px;">{{ ::item.sections[0] }}</h4>\n  <p>\n    The main purpose of this application is to help starting bass players with their learing process.\n    Application is highly focused on rhythm aspect of the music by using easy to understand timeline\n    representation with labels for proper counting. It can be used to create various rhythmic excercises,\n    drums backing tracks, or bass covers.\n  </p>\n\n  <h5>Before you start</h5>\n\n  <p>\n    Several topics of this user manual contains slide show animations, which are running only\n    when a particular topic is active (highlighted in the index section on the left side).\n    So when you scroll over the page content, take some care and check that appropriate topic is highlighted.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>\n    Application use HTML 5 Audio Web API for audio playback and works best in Blink/Webkit based browser like:\n    <ul>\n      <li><b>Chrome</b></li>\n      <li><b>Chromium</b></li>\n      <li><b>Opera</b></li>\n    </ul>\n\n  <p>\n    Web version of this application use browser\'s <a target="_blank" href="http://www.w3schools.com/html/html5_webstorage.asp">\n    local storage</a> for saving projects, so be careful with clearing browser\'s data. It also means that each browser has\n    independent workspace for storing data, and this workspace also depends on url used to serve this application. To move\n    projects between different workspaces, use Export/Import functions to write/read project files.\n  </p>\n\n  <p>\n    It is highly recommended to frequently save changes during editing. Also be aware, that save function is not applied to the whole project, but only to current section, and switching to other section without save\n    will results in loosing of last changes!\n  </p>\n</section>\n\n<section\n  id="section-2"\n  ng-controller="ToolbarController">\n  <h4>{{ ::item.sections[1] }}</h4>\n  <p>\n    Toolbar controls can be divided into the tree main groups:\n  </p>\n\n  <h5>Project controls</h5>\n  <div\n    layout="row"\n    class="control-panel md-whiteframe-3dp">\n    <div flex></div>\n    <div\n      layout="row"\n      ng-include="\'views/project_toolbar.html\'">\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <p>Contains mode switch to select between two application\'s modes:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>\n      <b><md-icon md-svg-icon="section-mode"></md-icon>Section mode</b> - for editing or playback of single section\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <b><md-icon md-svg-icon="playlist-mode"></md-icon>Playlist mode</b> - for creating and playback of multiple sections - playlists\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>\n    Depending on the selected mode, it contains selectbox with project\'s sections/playlists,\n    button to save actual section/all playlists, and menu with project and sections/playlists options.\n  </p>\n  <p class="md-indent">\n    <md-icon md-svg-icon="tip"></md-icon><em>Note: &nbsp;</em>\n    Selectbox has integrated function for text editing and items reorder. Click around\n    the arrow icon at right side to open selectbox, click on the selected item\'s text\n    to start text editing. To change order of items, open selectbox and use Drag & Drop\n    operation to move item to the new position.\n  </p>\n  <h5>Player controls</h5>\n  <div\n    layout="row"\n    class="control-panel md-whiteframe-3dp">\n    <div flex></div>\n    <div\n      ng-cloak\n      layout="row"\n      class="playback-fields"\n      ng-include="\'views/playback_toolbar.html\'">\n    </div>\n    <div flex></div>\n  </div>\n  <p>Allows to start, stop and configure playback (speed, range, repeating)</p>\n  <p class="md-indent">\n    <md-icon md-svg-icon="tip"></md-icon><em>Tip: &nbsp;</em>\n    Use <em>Visible screen playback </em><md-icon md-svg-icon="screen-playback"></md-icon>\n    or <em>Selection playback </em><md-icon md-svg-icon="selection-playback"></md-icon>\n    in combination with <a ng-click="scrollTo(3)">Barline</a> size adjustment to avoid automatic scrolling during playback for easier learning.\n  </p>\n\n  <h5>Track controls</h5>\n  <div class="control-panel md-whiteframe-3dp">\n    <div\n      ng-cloak\n      layout="row"\n      class="instruments-toolbar"\n      ng-include="\'views/tracks_toolbar.html\'">\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <p>\n    Allows to select active, configure and manage all instruments in the project. It also contains\n    a menu with volume preferences of all instruments (tracks), volume control for <em>Input Channel</em>\n    (when using microphone input), and special <em>Audio Track</em> channel.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <em>Audio Track</em> is useful in transcription process, to play original audio in the "background" synchronized with Section playback. \n  </p>\n</section>\n<section id="section-3">\n  <h4>{{ ::item.sections[2] }}</h4>\n\n  <p>\n    In the <b>Section mode</b>, Barline has several options for navigation and configuration within selected section.\n    When a section contains more bars than can fit to the screen, you can horizontally scroll with whole editor workspace\n    by swipe gestures on Barline area (use mouse on non-touch screens). You can also use player\'s progress slider,\n    which are useful especially for quick scrolling over large distances.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <b>Beats per Screen</b> is another very useful option that you can control with mouse - by scrolling with mouse wheel\n    (cursor must be inside Barline area). Alternatively, you can also set this option in <em>Layout Preferences</em> (bottom toolbar).\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Each project (composition) in this application should be composed from several smaller blocks called <b>Sections</b>.\n    Every section can have different bpm (tempo), time signature, length and few other settings. With the exception of bpm,\n    all these settings can be set in <em>Section Preferences</em> menu.\n  </p>\n  <br />\n  <div\n    layout="row"\n    class="slideshow"\n    style="margin: 0 16px;"\n    ng-controller="HelpBarController">\n\n    <div\n      class="section-preferences"\n      ng-include src="\'views/editor/section_preferences.html\'">\n    </div>\n\n    <div flex class="bar swiper-container">\n      <div class="swiper-wrapper">\n        <!-- Slides -->\n        <div\n          ng-repeat="slide in slides track by slide.id"\n          ng-attr-visible-subbeats="\n            {{ slide.beat.subdivision === 3? 3 : visibleSubbeats }}\n          "\n          class="swiper-slide bar-slide beat"\n          ng-class="::{ first: slide.beat.beat === 1 }">\n          <label class="bar-label">\n            {{ ::slide.beat.bar }}\n          </label>\n          <div\n            id="beat_{{ ::slide.beat.bar }}_{{ ::slide.beat.beat }}"\n            class="bar-beat"\n            layout="row"\n            ng-right-click="contextMenu.open($event, $index)"\n            ng-include src="\'views/editor/bar_beat.html\'">\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <br />\n\n  <p class="instructions">\n    Section mode controls:\n    <ul class="slideshow-steps">\n      <li>Use mouse swipe gestures or player\'s progress slider to scroll over visible beats of the section</li>\n      <li>Use mouse wheel for zoom-out/zoom-in:</li>\n      <ul><li>Scroll-up direction to raise number of visible beats on screen</li></ul>\n      <ul><li>Scroll-down direction to lower number of visible beats on screen</li></ul>\n      <li>Click on the time signature label to open Section preferences</li>\n      <li>Use right mouse button to open context menu for various bar/beat operations line Copy, Paste ...</li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n\n</section>\n'),n.put("views/help/bass.html",'<h4>{{ ::item.sections[0] }}</h4>\n\n<section id="section-1">\n  <p>\n    Sound Properties menu contains all properties used to describe individual bass sounds, like\n    playing style, note (type, pitch, length, ...) and volume. It also contains a playback function\n    for easy check of configured sound. You can open it by:\n    <ul>\n      <li>click on <div class="bass-button">+</div> button in bass editor area to create\n      a new sound at specified string and time (subbeat)</li>\n      <li>right click on existing bass sound element</li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n  <div\n  class="slideshow"\n    bd-help-bass-sheet="{\n      timeSignature: \'4/4\',\n      strings: \'EADG\',\n      controller: \'SoundPropertiesSlideshow\'\n    }">\n  </div>\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <br />\n  <p>\n    Even though this menu allows to edit all sounds properties, application offers keyboard\n    shortcuts and additional ways to create or edit sounds more effectively. Next topics will\n    cover this methods.\n  </p>\n  <p class="md-indent">\n    <md-icon md-svg-icon="tip"></md-icon><em>Note: &nbsp;</em>\n    Don\'t forget on functions available in <a ng-click="setHelpPage(helpPages[0], 3)">Barline</a> context menu, like <b>Copy</b>, <b>Paste</b>, <b>Clear</b> or beat subdivision options.\n  </p>\n</section>\n\n<section id="section-2">\n  <h4>{{ ::item.sections[1] }}</h4>\n  <p>\n    Drag & Drop operation can be used to:\n    <ul>\n      <li>Create a new sound by dragging particular note from fretboard</li>\n      <li>Move existing sound to the new position (string and time)</li>\n      <li>Copy existing sound to the new position - hold <b>Ctrl key</b> during dragging</li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n</section>\n\n<section id="section-3">\n  <h4>{{ ::item.sections[2] }}</h4>\n  <p>\n    Resize operation is executed by dragging resize handler - right side of the sound element.\n    It can be used to:\n    <ul>\n      <li>Change note length of the sound</li>\n      <li>Combine two sounds on the same string (regular notes with different pitch) into the slide sound</li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n\n  <div\n    class="slideshow"\n    bd-help-bass-sheet="{\n      timeSignature: \'4/4\',\n      strings: \'EADG\',\n      controller: \'ResizeSlideshow\'\n    }">\n  </div>\n\n  <p class="instructions">\n    Steps:\n    <ul class="slideshow-steps">\n      <h5>Resize operation:</h5>\n      <ul><li>1. Click and hold left mouse button on the right edge of the sound to start resize operation</li></ul>\n      <ul><li>2. Resize sound to the desired note length</li></ul>\n      <span></span>\n\n      <h5>Create slide:</h5>\n      <ul><li>1. Click and hold left mouse button on the right edge of the first sound to start resize operation</li></ul>\n      <ul><li>2. Resize first sound to overlap with the second sound</li></ul>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n</section>\n\n<section id="section-4">\n  <h4>{{ ::item.sections[3] }}</h4>\n  <p>\n    Some playling techniques like Hammer-On and Pull-Off require smooth transition from one note into the other one.\n    On the bass guitar it means playing two or more notes on single string pluck/stroke. Another reason to connect multiple\n    sounds is a Tie notation, where two or more notes are joined and played together with the time values summed.\n  </p>\n  <div\n    class="slideshow"\n    bd-help-bass-sheet="{\n      timeSignature: \'4/4\',\n      strings: \'EADG\',\n      controller: \'ComposedSounds\'\n    }">\n  </div>\n  <p class="instructions">\n    Steps:\n    <ul class="slideshow-steps">\n      <li>1. Create a first sound</li>\n      <li>2. Create a second sound on the same string (right after the first sound)</li>\n      <li>3. Select a second sound</li>\n      <li>4. Press <a ng-click="scrollTo(5)">keyboard shortcut</a> for particular sound transition type</li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n</section>\n\n<section id="section-5">\n  <h4>{{ ::item.sections[4] }}</h4>\n  <ul>\n    <li><b>Delete</b> - delete selected sound</li>\n    <li><b>+</b> - raise volume by 5%</li>\n    <li><b>-</b> - lower volume by 5%</li>\n    <li><b>Left</b> - reduce delay</li>\n    <li><b>Right</b> - add delay</li>\n    <h6>Regular notes:</h6>\n    <li><b>L</b> - switch note label (sharp -> flat, flat -> sharp)</li>\n    <li><b>Up</b> - raise note pitch by one semitone (fret)</li>\n    <li><b>Down</b> - lower note pitch by one semitone (fret)</li>\n    <li><b>.</b> - toggle staccato attribute</li>\n    <h6>Sounds transitions:</h6>\n    <li><b>H</b> - Hammer-On</li>\n    <li><b>P</b> - Pull-Off</li>\n    <li><b>R</b> - Let ring (Tie when both sounds have the same pitch, slide transition otherwise)</li>\n  </ul>\n</section>'),n.put("views/help/chords.html",'<section\n  id="section-1"\n  style="padding-top:44px;">\n  <h4 style="top:20px;">{{ ::item.sections[0] }}</h4>\n\n  <p>\n    You can increase the quality of bass tabs by entering chord information. The given benefits are:\n    <ul>\n      <li>Better logical structure and understanding of the composition</li>\n      <li>\n        Better visualization of notes being played on virtual fretboard in <em>Highlight view</em>,\n        so you can learn playing patterns more easily. It also works without active playback - click\n        on chord label to highlight all notes within this chord range.\n      </li>\n      <li>With double-click action on chord label (in <em>Section mode</em>), you can trigger playback\n        within chord range.\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n\n  <div ng-controller="ChordsController" ng-cloak>\n    <div class="bass-sheet strings-4 fret"></div>\n    <br />\n    <div>\n      <div ng-include="\'views/fret_diagram.html\'"></div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n</section>\n\n<section id="section-2">\n  <h4>{{ ::item.sections[1] }}</h4>\n  <p>\n    Chord information for current section can be assigned in <b>Chord Editor</b>,\n    accessible from <a ng-click="setHelpPage(helpPages[0], 3)">Section preferences</a> menu.\n    To add chord label, click on the <em>New</em> button and set following fields:\n  </p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><b>Chord</b>, composed of:</li>\n    <ul>\n      <li>\n        <em>Root note</em>\n        - name of the root note, for example: <em>Db, C#, ...</em>\n      <li>\n        <em>Type</em>\n        - type of the chord, for example: <em>maj, min, ...</em>\n      <li>\n        <em>Bass note</em>\n        - optional note name, used to define <em>Slash chord</em> - chord which\n        indicates emphasis of a bass note other than the root of the chord.\n    </ul>\n    <li><b>Position</b> defining start of the chord range, composed from bar, beat and subbeat index</li>\n  </ul>\n\n</section>\n'),n.put("views/help/drums.html",'<h4>{{ ::item.sections[0] }}</h4>\n\n<section id="section-1">\n  <p>\n    Drum and percussion editor is designed to be as simple as possible.\n    All sounds are described by single property - volume intensity.\n    Sound length (duration) depends only on particular drum type (sound sample).\n    Currently there is no option to untimely mute longer lasting sounds, but it is\n    planned to be implemented.\n  </p>\n  <p>&nbsp;</p>\n  <div\n    class="slideshow"\n    bd-help-drum-sheet="{\n      timeSignature: \'4/4\',\n      controller: \'DrumSounds\'\n    }">\n  </div>\n  <br />\n  <p class="instructions">\n    Basic sound editing controls:\n    <ul class="slideshow-steps">\n      <li>Click once to create loud drum sound</li>\n      <li>Click again to lower drum sound</li>\n      <li>Click again to clear drum sound</li>\n      <li>Use mouse wheel for more precise volume level control:</li>\n      <ul><li>Scroll-up direction to raise volume</li></ul>\n      <ul><li>Scroll-down direction to lower volume</li></ul>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n  <br />\n  <p class="md-indent">\n    <md-icon md-svg-icon="tip"></md-icon><em>Note: &nbsp;</em>\n    Don\'t forget on functions available in <a ng-click="setHelpPage(helpPages[0], 3)">Barline</a> context menu, like <b>Copy</b>, <b>Paste</b>, <b>Clear</b> or beat subdivision options.\n  </p>\n</section>\n\n<section id="section-2">\n  <h4>{{ ::item.sections[1] }}</h4>\n  <p>\n    Drag & Drop operation can be used to:\n    <ul>\n      <li>Move existing sound to the new position</li>\n      <li>Copy existing sound to the new position - hold <b>Ctrl key</b> during dragging</li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n</section>'),n.put("views/help/help.html",'<md-dialog\n  class="help-dialog"\n  ng-controller="HelpController">\n  <div class="dialog-header">\n    Help\n    <md-button\n      md-no-ink\n      class="dialog-close icon-hover"\n      ng-click="close()">\n      <md-icon md-svg-icon="x"></md-icon>\n    </md-button>\n  </div>\n\n  <md-dialog-content\n    layout="row"\n    ng-cloak\n    ng-init="\n      helpPages = [\n         {\n          template: \'views/help/app.html\',\n          title: \'Application\',\n          sections: [\n            \'Introduction\',\n            \'Toolbar\',\n            \'Barline\'\n          ]\n        }, {\n          template: \'views/help/bass.html\',\n          title: \'Bass guitar\',\n          sections: [\n            \'Sound Properties\',\n            \'Drag & Drop\',\n            \'Resize\',\n            \'Sounds transitions\',\n            \'Keyboard shortcuts\'\n          ]\n        }, {\n          template: \'views/help/drums.html\',\n          title: \'Drums/Percussions\',\n          sections: [\n            \'Creating sounds\',\n            \'Drag & Drop\'\n          ]\n        }, {\n          template: \'views/help/piano.html\',\n          title: \'Piano\',\n          sections: [\n            \'Keyboard shortcuts\'\n          ]\n        }, {\n          template: \'views/help/playlist.html\',\n          title: \'Playlists\',\n          sections: [\n            \'Creating and editing\'\n          ]\n        }, {\n          template: \'views/help/chords.html\',\n          title: \'Chord information\',\n          sections: [\n            \'General information\',\n            \'Creating and editing\'\n          ]\n        }\n      ]\n    "\n    class="help-container"\n    ng-class="[\'active-step-\'+index.activeStep]">\n    <div class="help-index">\n\n      <div\n        ng-repeat="item in ::helpPages"\n        class="index-item-container"\n        size="{{ ::item.sections.length }}"\n        ng-class="{expanded: page === item}">\n        <div\n          class="index-item"\n          ng-click="setHelpPage(item)">\n          {{ ::item.title }}\n        </div>\n        <ul\n          class="sections"\n          ng-if="page === item"\n          du-scroll-container="container-{{ ::$index }}">\n          <li\n            ng-repeat="section in ::item.sections"\n            href="#section-{{ ::$index+1 }}"\n            ng-click="selectSection($index + 1)"\n            ng-class="{selected: index.activeSection === $index + 1}"\n            du-smooth-scroll\n            du-scrollspy>\n            {{ ::section }}\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <md-content\n      flex\n      ng-repeat="item in ::helpPages"\n      ng-init="item.containerId = \'container-\'+$index"\n      id="{{ ::item.containerId }}"\n      class="content md-padding"\n      ng-show="item === page">\n      <div\n        flex\n        ng-if="item === page"\n        ng-include="::item.template"\n        class="help-content-page">\n      </div>\n    </md-content>\n  </md-dialog-content>\n</div>'),n.put("views/help/piano.html",'<h4>{{ ::item.sections[0] }}</h4>\n\n<section id="section-1">\n  <ul>\n    <li><b>Delete</b> - delete selected sound</li>\n    <li><b>Up</b> - raise note pitch by one semitone (fret)</li>\n    <li><b>Down</b> - lower note pitch by one semitone (fret)</li>\n    <li><b>.</b> - toggle staccato attribute</li>\n    <li><b>T</b> - create a tied note (with previous note)</li>\n    <li><b>L</b> - switch note label (sharp -> flat, flat -> sharp)</li>\n    <li><b>+</b> - raise volume by 5%</li>\n    <li><b>-</b> - lower volume by 5%</li>\n    <li><b>Left</b> - reduce delay</li>\n    <li><b>Right</b> - add delay</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <p>\n    Piano editor use similar drag & drop and resize operation for creating notes. Main difference is possibility to move/copy selected note to any other key position, thus changing the note pitch.\n    This feature is very useful for creating chord sounds, especially with several tied notes -\n    create tied notes in one key and then copy them with single drag & drop to other key(s).\n  </p>\n</section>\n'),n.put("views/help/playlist.html",'<section\n  id="section-1"\n  style="padding-top:44px;">\n  <h4 style="top:20px;">{{ ::item.sections[0] }}</h4>\n  <p>\n    Playlist is an ordered list of sections, where each section can be repeated multiple times.\n    Typically, every project should have at least one playlist for the whole composition,\n    but when your project is composed of many small section, it may be useful to create playlists\n    for bigger logical blocks like verses or choruses.\n  </p>\n  <p class="md-indent">\n    <md-icon md-svg-icon="tip"></md-icon><em>Note: &nbsp;</em>\n    Use can use Drag & Drop operation in <em>Playlists</em> selectbox to change order of project\'s playlists.\n  </p>\n  <br />\n  <p>\n    To open Playlist editor, you have to be in <b>Playlist Mode <md-icon md-svg-icon="playlist-mode"></md-icon></b>\n    and then click on <md-icon md-svg-icon="playlist-edit"></md-icon>.<br />\n    Playlist editor consists of two lists:\n    <ul>\n      <li>\n        <b>Playlist</b> - actual playlist\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <b>Section</b> - list of project\'s sections, but only the ones not already included\n        in the current playlist (for easier tracking of changes)\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n  <h5>Edit functions:</h5>\n  <p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Drag items (sections) from <b>Section</b> list into the <b>Playlist</b></li>\n      <li>\n        Drag items inside <b>Playlist</b> list to change order, or duplicate sections\n        in combination with pressed <b>Ctrl</b> key\n      </li>\n      <li>Enter number of repeats of particular section in text field (visible when hovering item)</li>\n      <li>Select and delete item in <b>Playlist</b> with <b>Delete</b> key</li>\n      <li>Use <b>Clear</b> button to remove all sections from current playlist</li>\n      <li>Use <b>Move all</b> button to move all project\'s sections into the playlist</li>\n    </ul>\n  </p>\n</section>')}]);